      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Setting up your spare Mac for Claude Code to control, a step-by-step guide",
      "url": "https://ykdojo.github.io/claude-controls-mac/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48959392",
      "score": 186,
      "comments": 135,
      "author": "ykev",
      "published": "2026-07-18T16:12:08Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Anthropic's Claude Code CLI agent executes commands directly, making dedicated, isolated hardware like a spare Mac ideal for secure execution.",
        "Local AI agents require broad shell access, raising risks of prompt injection, data loss, and unauthorized system modifications on primary devices.",
        "Isolating agentic workflows via SSH, Tailscale, or virtual machines mitigates the security dangers of arbitrary local code execution."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
