      "score": 27,
      "comments": 51,
      "author": "Diana",
      "published": "2026-07-18T16:25:19Z",
      "bullets": [
        "High-volume AI code generation causes developer cognitive fatigue, making manual code review an ineffective defense against subtle logic bugs.",
        "AI models frequently introduce hallucinated dependencies and security vulnerabilities that standard PR reviews fail to catch reliably.",
        "Shifting the burden of AI-generated code to human reviewers creates QA bottlenecks and increases long-term technical debt."
      ]
    },
